Detailed Description

BtCompoundDataElement represents data elements that consist of other data elements. These data elements can be basic data elements or again compound data elements. There are two kinds of compound data elements: data element sequences and alternate data elements. Data element sequences describe a composition of two or more data elements, an alternate data element describes a selection of two or more data elements. Seclection means that the data element describes two or more posibilities of values a data element can hold. The BtCompoundDataElement is the owner of its sub data elements and maintains the memory for these. This means, that the inserted sub data elements are not copied, only the pointer to the data element is stored in the BtCompoundDataElement. So the memory for the data element has to be allocated by the user, but the destruction of the memory is done by the BtCompoundDataElement.

BtSddbDataElement * BtSddbDeContainer::Delete (  const BtSddbDataElement *  data_element  ) 
 

Delete deletes the passed data element from this data element and returns the data element following the deleted one or 0 if the the deleted one was the last. The deleted element is also destroyed, so the passed pointer gets invalid.

Parameters:
date_element A reference to a pointer to a BtDataElement that should be deleted. The pointer is set to 0 if the element is was in this data element and could be deleted.
Returns:
A pointer to a BtDataElement pointing to the sub data element following to one that was deleted.

0 The data element that has to be deleted was the last one or was not contained in this data element. Check data_element to disdinguish these two cases.
